<Class name="CMIF_CommercialQueryHeader" id="c9f79062-8c84-4133-8670-35a754ac5b06">
    <superclass name="CMIF_CommercialQueryEntity"/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <text>There is a requirement for DCT Gdansk Commercial staff to access the JMT Application and easily obtain information on customer activity.  A customer could be an Operator or a Freight Forwarder

The Commercial Enquiry Screen is now available on the menu Navigator under the General Functions and is licensed under the KPI module.

The class is used to store all the user input selection from the Searcher and to process the information further on according to the requirements.

Case Scenario - Commercial Enquiry:
The user would like to know how many transactions have been performed in a time range OR for a voyage against a set of cargo items(containers, cars etc.).
	The selection criteria is by default:
		Time settings 	: 	first day of the current month - current day
		CargoType 		: 	ISOContainer
		Services 		:	All Release/Receive TiTransactions.(hard coded in self.populateTiTypesByDefault())
	Additional Searcher options:
		FreightForwarder
		Services
		Operators
The Search option is processed by : doQuery() 
If a voyage is selected in the Time Settings tab then the date range will be ignored and the search will be performed in the: doQueryByVoyage() method, otherwise the search criteria will be run against the time range selected (doQueryByDate2).
</text>
